social_posts.post_text: @nevs_barbecue has arrived! 🔥 They celebrated their dream come to life this Monday with a Grand Opening in Promenade Plaza 🥳 Served counter style, choose from classics like Burnt Ends, Sliced Brisket, Pulled Pork, Cracked Black Pepper Sausage, Pulled Chicken 🔪 Congrats fam & wishing you many years of success!! 👏🏼 #eatpalmbeach

Surprised my mom with such a bright & beautiful tropical flower arrangement by @rosiegirlflorals for her birthday this weekend! 💐 Rebecca is the sweetest and made it so special with just a couple hints about what she likes! (Plus she delivers 🤩) My mom loved it. 💞 Check her out in Jupiter @rosiegirlflorals! #eatpalmbeach #supportlocal #locallove

⚽️ USA vs Netherlands 🇺🇸
Today at 10am!! Have you been watching the World Cup?? Did you know @dasbeergarden was named a Top 100 to watch at by Yelp and Fox Soccer? 🍻 We stopped in for Brazil vs Cameroon & Switzerland vs Serbia yesterday 🇧🇷 They’re adjusting their hours for games so check before you go! 
GO USA ❤️🤍💙 #eatpalmbeach

Another @pbfoodwinefest in the books! 📚 I can’t wait to share all of the amazing details but for now here is a peek of the grind that is #PBFWF! 👀 26 events over 4 days from @fspalmbeach to @thebraziliancourt @eaupalmbeach to @buccanpalmbeach  @stagekitchen @avocadogrill to @pbc_conventioncenter to @cafechardonnay and morrrrre! 🗺️ I can’t say enough about @davidsabin and @lindsay_autry and what they accomplish with this event each year. What they’ve evolved this festival into and the talent (in and out of the kitchen) and sponsors they’ve brought to PBC. 🌴 It’s truly something special. The relationships that have been cultivated are incredible, the memories are forever, and the food and drink is just next level. ⬆️ I’m so proud of them and of the team - people like @vbarit and emcees @andywieseneck & @theduerr and photogs like @traceybensonphotography and @alissadragunphoto and videographers like @keymomentfilms and sooo many others - that’s proof that team work makes the dream work. ✨ I’m honored to be a part of such a stand out weekend for our area - and beyond! 🍽️🍷 Thank you to all of the phenomenal chefs who came to town and showed out 👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼 Thank you to all of the sponsors who support PBFWF and the event goers who bring high energy and good vibes 🙏🏼Much love and go get some rest!! 😴 #eatpalmbeach

Have to share because I’ve been noticing @theoliverthomas popping up all over my life. 😍 For one, I love my 24+7 tennis bag. Perfect size, great compartments, the color is so lovely and it stays super clean. 🎾 They have it in a Lavender color now too which looks gorg 💜 I’ve been rocking this Bestie Baguette crossbody for the past couple weeks and love it. Side pouch for my phone and easy access flap is currently making it beat out my disco bag for every day wear. 👜 And the Picnic Backpack is the cutest cooler bag and so convenient! 🎒 It’s great for beach / boat days, playground picnics, or even just bringing cool items over to a friends house. 👏🏼 Had to contain myself during their last sale because the weekender duffle is calling my name 🙈 #eatpalmbeach #oliverthomas #teamoliverthomas

POURATORIUM // @pumphousecoffeeroasters revealed their Pouratorium in West Palm Beach and it is a vision come to life 💙 Serving coffee, espresso, food, wine & beer the bevvies flow and so do the vibes ✌🏼 Featuring a coffee bar, roasting production floor, lab, bar, lounge, and table seating the space is bustling but cozy, AM to PM ☕️🍻🍷 There are no words for how proud I am of Alex and Christian, their killer team, and the determination (blood, sweat, tears, sleepless nights included) to be leaders in the coffee space in South Florida and beyond. 🌴 I can’t wait to see what this new venue becomes and to watch them grow even more. ⬆️ Go visit them, check out the space, have some delicious coffee, and support some of the hardest working, most passionate people I know. 👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼 And not gonna lie, you’ll run into some amazing movers and shakers in our area there. Good people attract good people. ✨ #eatpalmbeach #pumphousecoffeeroasters

New year. New goals. New priorities. ✨ I hope everyone had a great 2022 filled with love and success. Best wishes for a prosperous 2023!🥂 

Friendly reminder: Social media is a highlight reel. Don’t judge your life based off what others present. Be proud of your accomplishments, be grateful for the gifts life brings, and enjoy the journey you’re on. Use the new year to set your sights and venture on. 🗺️ Sending good vibes and wishing you all the best 🤙🏼 #eatpalmbeach

MANATEE LAGOON // The cold snap has @manateelagoon bustling with manatees ❄️ We took the girls and had a beautiful morning watching over a dozen sea cows make their way along the veranda 💙 They are a gentle animal, coasting along and coming up for air every few minutes. We saw a cow and calf which was so sweet, toured the exhibits, pressed some souvenir pennies, and snagged a couple marinelife stuffies from the gift shop. Don’t miss out on the top deck where you can catch an expansive view of the waterway and birds eye vantage point of the action! 🌊 If you’re trying to time your visit I totally recommend the manatee cam at VisitManateeLagoon.com to get a sneak peek! 👀 Such a cool eco-discovery center by @insidefpl 💡 Plus admission is FREE! 🤩 #eatpalmbeach

Prepare for some Delray Beach content this week! 🌴

This trip was a totally unsponsored girls getaway so the time spent photoing was less than usual but still 🔥🔥🔥 and I have to share!! 

We stayed at @therayhotel and I have thoughts… 

STAFF: Phenomenal!! Over the top nice, attentive, available. Gwen and her crew checked us in, Peter and his wife were our bell staff, the ladies working at Stingers were so sweet ☕️, we snagged a pre-dinner cocktail at @akirabackdelray and our bartender was top notch. Valet were the nicest guys. I can’t stress how great everyone was enough. 

FOOD: Illy coffee downstairs was much needed, lunch/light bites at @rosewaterdelray (shown) was perfection and we loved the rooftop outdoor seating. 

ROOMS: Well appointed, clean, comfy beds, all good things. 

LOCATION: Awesome for walking to everything. We shopped the Ave, walked to happy hour, dinner, breakfast. Didn’t touch the cars between check in and out. 

This is a @hilton property and I totally recommend it. Would absolutely stay there again (in a heartbeat). 

#eatpalmbeach

I don’t get down to Delray nearly as much as I’d like to, so the hit list was hot and heavy 🔥 And @dadadelray was right at the top for dinner. 🍽️

We had such a delicious time. The weather was perfection for outdoor dining, the Mojito menu was hefty, and we shared an array of plates - from the Dada Dates and Mediterranean Mezze to the Vegan Butternut Squash and Bolognese 🥄 

Everyone always seems focused on the “new and exciting” but there is something to be said for the tried and trues. Restaurants that survive decades should never be overlooked imo. 👀 There’s a reason they’ve seen it all and are still standing. ✨

#eatpalmbeach

Did I do it right??? 🤷🏼‍♀️

#itsgonnabemay

Popped into @amarbakeryandmarket strolling the Ave and had to try the bagel cronut 🥯 

We fell in love with this bakery and market featuring Mediterranean goodies and a drool-worthy case of pastries and baked goods. 🥐 Plus they serve @pumphousecoffeeroasters so you know they’re top notch 🔝☕️ 

@amardelray is definitely on my list for my next visit 🫒

#eatpalmbeach #amardelray

Checked out the new @guacago on Dixie in WPB 🥑

I’ve had their guac at events like ArtiGras and Honda Classic and was curious to see what the brick and mortar would entail. The answer - guac (duh) - but also some delicious bowls and wraps! 🥗

I built the OG guac with chicken into a wrap. It was fresh, delicious, and easy to eat on the run 🌯 The manager was crazy nice and humored me along the line like a baby deer lost in the woods 😅

Great spot to grab n’ go or have a quick bite. I was in and out in like 5 min and made it to my meeting on time - winning!! ⭐️

Have you been??? 

#eatpalmbeach

Happy Mother’s Day! 💞

To all the moms out there - you’re doing great. The days are long, but the years fly by. And most of them feel like a rollercoaster. 🎢

These little girls changed me the minute they entered my life. My goals, hopes, and dreams, my fears and sleepless nights, my highest highs and lowest lows. They are my biggest accomplishment and at the end of the day my entire world. 🌎 All I can hope is that I raise them right and that they rest their head on their pillow every night knowing how loved they are.✨

Thank you to my mom for helping me so much along my motherhood journey. There’s no one like Nana. 👩🏼

To all the women out there who have lost a child or struggled to conceive, to those who have lost their mother or have a heaviness in their heart today, sending lots of love your way 🙏🏼💙

#happymothersday #eatpalmbeach

#NeverForget // There are moments, visuals, and emotions of 9/11/01 that I will never be able to erase from my mind. The confusion, the fear, the sadness, the anger. The second plane, the bodies falling, the towers collapsing, the calls from Flight 93. The heroes, the unity, watching them raise the flag amongst the rubble. 🇺🇸 New York will never be the same for me. Watching the planes cross over the courts of the US Open was even eerie. But we rebuilt, we came back taller and stronger, we were unified as a nation in a way I’ll also never be able to forget. A shining light in the dust and darkness.✨ Today I remember those who lost their lives. That day, in the days that followed, in the battles that followed years later. Saying a prayer for those still affected, those families and friends who lost loved ones, the survivors. All of us. ❤️🤍💙

#911 #september11 #sept11 #nyc #newyorkcity

Join Me at Highballs & Hibiscus! 🍸🌺
 
September 23, 2023
6:30PM | @eaupalmbeach
 
For an evening of food, fun, philanthropy.. and dancing! 🍽️🥳🩷💃🏼🕺🏼 
 
Benefiting Women’s & Children’s services at @JupiterMedicalCenter 🏥 
 
JMC holds a special place in my heart, as that is where I delivered both of my girls 👧🏼👧🏼 and have had the never-fun trips to the ER with them. 🤕 It means everything to a parent to know your children are in good hands, so I am beyond grateful for the services we have so close by at JMC. 
 
As a North County resident, our family has seen a lot of JMC over the years, and I am always thrilled to hear about their news, whether it's plans to expand or add offerings, or enrich their current services. It’s a beautiful facility with great staff that have been with us through days of overwhelming joy and fear from the delivery room to the ICU. 
 
Excited to support this event and @jupitermedicalcenterfoundation 🙏🏼 Plus we get to have an amazing time in the process - win / win!! 🙌🏼
 
🍒 To top it all off, anyone who has already purchased a ticket OR buys one between now and Monday at Midnight ✨ will be entered to win a hotel stay at Eau Palm Beach Resort & Spa for the night of the event!! Eau is gorgeous if you’ve never been. Like 5-star, award-winning fantastic. ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

I met the guys behind @munyonspawpaw a little while back and was thrilled to walk into 2 of my favorite restaurants this month and see it behind their bars! 🥃

This refreshing aperitif pays homage to Dr. James Munyon and his original Munyon’s Paw-Paw formulation, dating back to 1903 (and featured in @111places Palm Beach!) 📚

It features a blend of all kinds of goodies including papaya (paw paw) allspice, bitter orange, cane sugar, hibiscus, ginger, and pink grapefruit. 🍊

I asked @mix.with.max at @eat.coolinary to test out a Paw Paw Spritz and - move over, Aperol!! So light, refreshing, and delicious🍹 I don’t even care that it’s Fall, and am without question making this my Summer 2024 drink so mark your calendars ☀️ It can also be used to jazz up a martini, old fashioned, mule, paloma.. and give it a Palm Beach twist 🌴

I tried it out again last night at @barcellonpb and yet again got looks from everyone at the bar and the “what exactly is that?” 👀 

Anyways!! Had to share!! So fun and always love to see locals thriving 🌱 I did also see their bottles in @totalwine at @shoplegacyplace 🛒

Cheers! 🥂

Finally made our way to @amardelray on Atlantic Ave in @downtowndelray and what a night ✨

We took the advice of the sommelier starting with glasses of Lebanese wine - rosé and a red blend 🍷

The Hummus with Lamb was delicious served with warm pita while the Labneh proved to be my condiment of choice throughout the entire meal 🤍 

We shared a Rocca Beet Salad which was piled high with red beets 🥗 and the Fried Kibbeh served with a mint cucumber yogurt for dipping 🥒

For our entree we split the Steak Kebab which was so flavorful and a beautiful plate with warm rice and vegetables 🥩

The atmosphere was fantastic. The music was transportive and relaxing, the vibe is chill but energetic. You can see the wood fire over from the dining room and the decor is simple while drawing your eye to details 🪴 

We had such a nice date night and both agreed a return visit is needed. 💞

#amardelray #eatpalmbeach #delraybeach #atlanticave #downtowndelray

Today is my 39th birthday. It’s also the 10 year anniversary of #EatPalmBeach. 🥳

10 years is hard to believe. But when I look back it makes total sense. This page, this account, this community has changed my life. 

I’ve met incredible people, eaten amazing food, been to outstanding events, and achieved some of the biggest goals of my life through EPB. I have started businesses, chaired events, written columns, published a book, been featured on TV, in magazines, on the radio, on podcasts. I’ve told my story through food and my hometown, becoming a mom, and navigating life. I’ve been able to give back to my community in meaningful ways. It’s honestly been a dream. ☁️

And it’s all because of you. Thank you. For following, for liking, for shaping this page from day one. There really are no words that fully grasp my gratitude for what you have given me and my family. This platform has been magical in many ways. ✨

I hope you all have enjoyed the past ten years. And I hope the new year brings a wave of creativity and fresh air. 🌱 It hasn’t always been easy keeping up, staying true, and finding my place in this space. But I promise I’m always trying. 

Thanks again everyone. Love, Cristyle 🩵

For the past 10 years or so, in lieu of a New Year’s resolution, I have created a dream board of all of the goals I hope to accomplish in the next year. 🗺️

They have been business-driven, personal, financial, introspective. Small things like cooking more and cursing less, big things like having a baby or buying a house. 🥘🏡

No matter the size or importance of the goal every year on New Year’s I look back and see how I did. And it always amazes me that I hit the goals. 🎯

This year we got the car we’ve talked about for years (had never been on the board before), we bought a house on our dream street (had oddly not added it to the board although we aimlessly searched for the past few years), I made the D2 tennis team, got my boaters license, hit my income goal, carved out time for my girls, and focused on building friendships. 🚙🏠🎾⛵️🏦💞 

The only goals I had to second guess myself on were the ones about taking care of myself.. finding contentment, embracing happiness. ✨ I know I tried. But I think I failed. And I think those may need a larger space this year. To trickle down across my entire life, onto my girls, and family, and friends. To reinvigorate my business, my creativity, and bring a level of calm and joy to each day. 🙏🏼

I hope you take a moment to review this past year and look forward to the year ahead. It can be eye opening what your mind and heart focus in on and prioritize. 

Wishing everyone a happy and prosperous new year. 🎉

#eatpalmbeach

Finally made it in to dine at @hibiscusstreatery! 🌺 I’ve had their catering at a few different events and I’ve always been a fan of Little Moir restaurants. 

The eatery is a handful of tables located inside their market and catering location in Jupiter. The vibe is chill and intimate with SFL colors and feel. 🌴

The menu featured some fan favorites along with items I haven’t seen at leftovers or food shack. I went with the ahi bowl which was more of a stack and absolutely delicious. Other dishes at the table were the lobster mac & cheese - yum! - sweet potato crusted fish - duh! -, and pork belly tacos 🐟🦞🌮 We also split the conch fritter appetizer. So good.

We had a solid laugh in the parking lot because someone noticed me and called me out for not getting the tuna basil roll! Absolutely hysterical and totally true because the only reason we didn’t get it is because I was having ahi for my meal 😂😂

Such a great little spot. And also cool that you can grab some deliciousness to go from the market like smoked fish dip, seafood salads, etc. 

Not gonna lie. My sister and her husband went back again the next night. We like what we like. 🤷🏼‍♀️

#eatpalmbeach

Loving the new @elacurryandcocktails location! 🫶🏼

Located just a few doors down from their previous home, ELA has expanded into @theshopsofdrv with a lounge bar and dining room, private room for 20, outdoor seating, and Peacock Tiki Bar 🦚

The weather was too perfect to not sit outside ✨ We ordered Pani Puri to start with Paratha, Butter Chicken, Niman Pork Vindaloo (🔥), and Kerala Beef Short Rib 🥘 

@bootleggregcocktails is at it again so we had to try the Perfecta Cuba Libre 🥃 They have a great cocktails and spirits selection so I jumped at the chance to have a @munyonspawpaw Spritz 🍹 

The girls always asked for ELA take out so was awesome to have such a great space to dine as a family. 

So excited for @pushkarry & @andystagepga! Beautifully done guys! 👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼

#eatpalmbeach #elacurrykitchen #elacurryandcocktails

This weekend we visited the newly opened @pinksteakwpb by @chefjuliengremaud 🦩

Walking in, the atmosphere is elevated and sexy but playful with pops of pink, green and gold, a large flamingo taking center stage in the dining room. The vibe is intimate and energetic with servers buzzing through the space in hats, diners eager to try the newest hotspot. 

Dinner was a delight. We started with sushi - the Pink Steak, Two Step Tuna & Avocado Himachi 🍣, House and Caesar Salads 🥗, Crispy Rock Shrimp 🍤 and Beef Tartare 🥩 For our entrees we tried a myriad of steaks, the creamed spinach, patatas bravas, roasted cauliflower, and fresh black truffle fries 🍽️

Both the cocktail and wine lists had something for everyone 🍸🍷 Sadly we didn’t not make it to dessert given we tried half the menu for dinner. 🍨

The service was fantastic and Chef Julien was beaming in the kitchen. ✨

Wishing them much success. Though judging from how tough a reservation is to come by, I think they’ll be more than fine. 👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼

#eatpalmbeach #pinksteak
